# Exercise 7: Define variables and create a plot using labs().

# Plotting Unemployed vs. Population

```{r}
plot <- ggplot(data = economics, aes(x = pop, y = unemploy)) + geom_point()

plot + 
labs(title = "US Unemployment vs. Population Growth", 
x = "Total Population (thousands)",
y = "Number of Unemployed (thousands)")

```

